¿Qué tipo de datos contiene la columna?

Cifras de población o número de casos

Lugares

Resultados de encuestas o evaluaciones

Organizaciones humanitarias (financiadores, agencias, ONG)

Respuesta humanitaria (actividades, clusters, etc.)

Crisis o eventos (por ejemplo, incidentes de seguridad)

Fechas

Programación de cash o información financiera

Indicadores humanitarios generales

Metadatos que describen la fila de datos (por ejemplo, la fuente de los datos)

Ninguna de las anteriores

What is the humanitarian context?

General population (including those not affected by the crisis)

Affected by the crisis (including those not in need of assistance)

In need of humanitarian assistance (including those not targeted)

Targeted for humanitarian assistance (including those not yet reached)

Actually reached with humanitarian assistance

#geo +lat

The preferred format for latitude is a decimal value, e.g. "8.5" instead of "8 30.0N".

You are free to add more attributes, or to make up your own, if you need to make further distinctions.

#geo +lon

The preferred format for longitude is a decimal value, e.g. "-75.5" instead of "75 30.0W".

You are free to add more attributes, or to make up your own, if you need to make further distinctions.

◀️ Retroceso Reiniciar 📖 HXL dictionary

Finished!

#geo +latlon

You are free to add more attributes, or to make up your own, if you need to make further distinctions.

#date

The preferred date format is YYYY-MM-DD, e.g. "2019-04-01". You may also abbreviate to just the month ("2019-04") or just the year ("2019").

How is your overall dataset shaped?

#indicator

Note that if your dataset contains many columns of indicators, you do not have to tag all of them. Add hashtags only to the columns that people might want to be able to work on using HXL-aware tools.

It is wide, with multiple columns of indicator values in each row

It is narrow and long, with one indicator value in each row, together with the indicator's name or code

#x_???

Los hashtags básicos de HXL no pueden describir todos los tipos especializados de datos humanitarios. Si no puede encontrar ninguna coincidencia para lo que necesita etiquetar, puede crear un hashtag personalizado que comience con "# x_", p. Ej. "# x_virulence".

You are free to add more attributes, or to make up your own, if you need to make further distinctions.
